Hi Debian Med team,

thank you all for joining the bug squashing party.  I think we cleaned
up the list of bugs quite a bit.  The last round of freshly filed bugs
was cleaned up quite quickly - thank you for working on this so busily.

I personally became a bit distracted the last couple of days.  I'll
be a bit distracted by my family until start of next year.  Than I try
to work on testing migrations and upgrading packages to their latest
upstream versions to make sure our set of packages will be up to date
for the freeze.

Thanks again for all your work and have some nice days
   Andreas.


